    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Religious buildings of Southeast Asian origin used as assembly halls or sanctuaries containing an altar and Buddhist images. Buddhist monastery; medieval Jaina temple; vasatī; monastery (sometimes with sanctum). For the general term for a temple or monastery complex, use "viharas (religious communities)."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
